- Minecraft Java Server on Proxmox (Fabric) -

https://ubuntu.com/download
-> Download the .ISO

On Proxmox
(left hand side) -> local (Device name) > ISO Images > Upload > Select: Ubuntu ISO > Upload it
Create VM > Node: default > VM ID: default > Name: (Name)
          Storage: local > ISO Image: Ubuntu > Type: Linux > Version: Latest one
          System = Leave everything as default
          Disks = Disk size: set to 40
          CPU = Set the cores to 4 (depend on how much you can handle)
          Memory = 4096
          Network = Leave as default
          Confirm = Finish

To start and install Ubuntu:
  Left-hand side > 100 (minecraft) > Start > Console
  Ubuntu installation > Setup it as you need

After setting up and installation
Terminal: sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y

Install what type of server you want:
Fabric: sudo apt install openjdk-21-jdk -y

To check what version you have: java -version

Create a folder for Minecraft Server:
mkdir minecraft-server
cd minecraft-server

Download the Fabric Server:
wget https://maven.fabricmc.net/net/fabricmc/fabric-installer/1.0.1/fabric-installer-1.0.1.jar

Install the Fabric Installer:
java -jar fabric-installer-1.0.1.jar server -mcversion 1.21 -downloadMinecraft

Accept the EULA:
echo "eula=true" > eula.txt

To start the server:
java -Xmx5G -Xms2G -jar fabric-server-launch.jar nogui

Now the server is running:
Open another Terminal and typer "ip a" to find the ip address to be used

How to stop: Type "stop" in the game server Terminal

How to make the server run automatically:
sudo nano /etc/systemd/system/minecraft.service
| | | | | | | | Enter it in | | | | | | | | |
V V V V V V V V             V V V V V V V V V
[Unit]
Description=Minecraft Fabric Server
After=network.target

[Service]
User=minecraft
WorkingDirectory=/home/minecraft/minecraft-server
ExecStart=java -Xmx5G -Xms2G -jar fabric-server-launch.jar nogui
Restart=on-failure

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target

Run these commands to reload, start on boot, and start it immediately.
sudo systemctl daemon-reload
sudo systemctl enable minecraft
sudo systemctl start minecraft

Check server status:
sudo systemctl status minecraft

Finally, reboot the server and check if everything works:
sudo reboot

**Now this is just on a local level
______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

Now it will be transformed to a WAN server (This will expose your IP address, be safe :)

Log into your router to Port Forward the server:

Look for Port Forwarding or New Rule
Internal IP: Choose your server IP
Protocol: TCP
Internal & External Port 25565

Go to: https://whatismyip.com (check your public ip)

Server Address to join will be: [public IP address]:25565

______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

How to add mods? **Make sure they are .jar files**

Go to your preferred Minecraft Mod distributor: Modrenth/Forge/etc

Look for mods that are compatible with your server: Fabric/NeoForge/Forge AND game version

Download the .jar files

On the Proxmox Ubuntu VM, open the Terminal:

(Stops the minecraft server)
sudo systemctl stop minecraft 

(Make a new directory to upload the mods)
mkdir -p /home/minecraft/minecraft-server/mods

(Go back to your actual computer and download the mod that fits your version and type)
Use this prompt for in the Command Prompt:
scp C:\Users\Username\Downloads\modfile.jar minecraft@privateIPaddress:/home/minecraft/minecraft-server/mods/

